        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. being male or assigned male at birth (YTW);

          2. identifying as a man who has sex with men (YMSM) and/or gay bisexual man or
             transgender woman/transwoman;

          3. identifying as African American/Black, Hispanic/Latino, and/or as a racial/ethnic
             minority or person of color;

          4. 16-24 years old;

          5. English-speaking (primary);

          6. currently unemployed, but seeking employment;

          7. considered "at-risk" for HIV based on risk assessment (2-item pre-screen); and

          8. able to attend a 4-session employment program.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Individuals identifying as non-Hispanic White; or

          2. Individuals not assigned male at birth
